(1)
1562 Flatbush Ave., west side, between Aves. H and I, showing the A.H. Hubbard house, which was demolished in 1925. If located in 1937, it would be in East 32nd Street, and about 170 feet north of Ave. I. It formerly stood on the Flatbush Turnpike, which became AmersFort Place at this point in 1919. In 1929, the Montgomery Royal Tennis Courts were on the site.

1922.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

(2)
The same, a side and rear view.

1923.

Eugene L. Armbruster collection.

(3)
The same, showing the side and front.

March 1925.

Eugene L. Armbruster collection.

(4)
The same, showing also an outbuilding.

April 1922.

Eugene L. Armbruster collection.
